    One major property of graphs is <em>adjacency</em>. 
    <em>Adjacency</em> occurs when two arbitrary vertices <var>U</var> and <var>V</var> are on the same edge {<var>U</var>, <var>V</var>}. 
    In the graph on the right, vertices <var>A</var> and <var>B</var> are adjacent because they both belong on the edge {<var>A</var>, <var>B</var>}. 
